It places more focus on immersive gameplay than it does on seamless gameplay.
Which is ironic, as the constant little things they do to be "immersive" kind of take me out of the experience.
I would value immersiveness over seamless gameplay though, personally

One of the big bears that I mentioned earlier was that the main character puts away his weapons every time he gets on a horse, and in order to re-equip them you have to again go into the equipment menu and do it again.
This gets real old real quick, especially when you jumped off your horse to defend yourself from bandits/bounty hunters and find yourself with only your pistol.
So you have to meander on over to your horse to get your guns out again, but good luck with having your horse stay alive as it gets shot and suffers perma-death.
It isnt just like, one button press to get your weapons out?
Nope, you can only carry so many weapons at a time, (pistol, 2 long weapons, and a melee) and everything but your pistol gets put away when you ride a horse.
Oh, and when you whistle for your horse, it comes to you in real time.
So if you left it 500 meters away, pull out a nice book to read while it comes back.
And if you get too far away from the horse, it doesn't come at all.\
Yeah, I never had a problem with the assassins creed "your house just spawns 30 feet away" technique
It's especially pleasurable when it decides to just walk to you instead of at least trotting.
Yeah, and Witcher 3 as well. It just teleports right behind you.
Almost named my horse "Roach" but decided against it.
Alas, Horsey McHorseface was too long.
That would also be very convinient
Ah, and there's not really any fast travel either.
Also, Mark’s was trying to find the horse call button & I’m not sure he’s figured it out yet
Technically there is, but you need to spend a lot of money on upgrading your camp first, and you then can only teleport from your camp to a town you've already visited.
You can't go from town to town.
You can auto-pilot on your horse, but that can be interrupted by random encounters.
And you can take a coach or a train, but everything is in real time.

Ah, and I hope you like being a good Samaritan, because the honor system flat out locks you out of certain missions if your honor isn't high enough and just generally makes the game easier for the player by giving them discounts on everything.
Oh, and the bounty system is dumb as bricks.

Any time you have a bounty in state limits, you can and will be mercilessly hunted by a giant posse that are very good at killing. And when they kill you, it does nothing to take away from your bounty, they just steal your money.
The ONLY way to get rid of a bounty is to pay it off.
